"Measure for multi-faceted channel" under fire
 &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, April 11 (KCNA) -- Associate Prof. and master Ri U Gap, a member of the Consultative Council of Former South Korean Politicians in the North for the Promotion of Peaceful Reunification, disclosed in an interview with KCNA on April 9 the reactionary nature of the "measure for multi-faceted channel for assistance to the north" loudly advertised nowadays by the South Korean authorities.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   The "measure" is no more than a drama orchestrated by  the anti-national separatists  who are undesirous of genuine cooperation between the fellow countrymen and the improvement of inter-Korean relations, he said.   Ri went on to say:&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; I worked as a university professor in the north and south Jolla provinces, South Korea, for many years.  I know that the present South Korean chief executive resorted to deceptive tactics whenever he was driven to the corner while he was active as an opposition leader.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   The "measure for multi-faceted channel"  is aimed at pacifying the growing desire of the South Korean people for reunification and alliance with communism and the north.   If the authorities of the "government for the people" truly want dialogue and improvement of inter-Korean relations they should unconditionally and immediately implement the priorities proposed by the joint meeting of the government, political parties and the organizations in the North Korea."

Overseas Koreans commemorate Sun's Day
 &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, April 11 (KCNA) -- Overseas Koreans are significantly commemorating Sun's Day, the birthday of the President Kim Il Sung.   A joint meeting for commemorating Sun's Day was held in Moscow on Wednesday by the United Confederation of Koreans in Russia, the United Confederation of Koreans in Moscow, the Korean Veterans Organization in Moscow and the Association of Koreans in Moscow.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   A reporter and speakers at the meeting highly praised the immortal revolutionary exploits of President Kim Il Sung, stressing that it is  joy, happiness and honor of the progressive humankind of the world as well as the Korean people to commemorate Sun's Day significantly.   They expressed the firm determination to actively contribute to the building of a powerful state in the socialist homeland under the leadership of the respected Marshal Kim Jong Il and to the cause of national reunification.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   A letter to Kim Jong Il was adopted at the meeting.   Meanwhile, a seminar of Korean social scientists in Japanï¿½@was held in Tokyo on the same day to mark Sun's Day.

Sun of loyalty and filial piety
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, April 11 (KCNA) -- A member of the Sun Society of South Korea Nam Hyok released an article titled "Sun of loyalty and filial piety" on the threshold of Sun's Day, according to Seoul-based radio Voice of National Salvation.   The article says:&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;The leader Kim Jong Il is the sun of loyalty and filial piety, who advanced the idea of loyalty and filial piety for the first time in history and has built a country pervaded with loyalty and filial piety in the North Korea by carrying  the idea into practice.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   The sun illuminates the world with rays of loyalty and filial piety and these rays represent the idea of loyalty and filial piety.    Kim Jong Il expounded a new conception of loyalty and filial piety, saying that they are a trait inherent in a soldier faithful to the leader and the expression of filial piety is used in a way to underscore the  aspect of the sense of moral obligation in loyalty though it stems from loyalty.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   His definition of the idea of loyalty and filial piety is an undying exploit performed  by him to be recorded in the human history of thought.    The sun inspires the people with  warmth of loyalty and filial piety and it precisely means practice of loyalty and filial piety.   Kim Jong Il's  loyalty and filial piety towards President Kim Il Sung is a genuine model of loyalty and filial piety that can hardly be found in any society of the world and history book.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   Kim Jong Il created the history of loyalty and filial piety in defending the President when he was alive and accomplished the noble cause for the immortality of the President after his demise.    The north is a flower garden of loyalty and filial piety tended by the sun for the sun of loyalty and filial piety enables all people to live always with joy and in warmth free from shade and tundra. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
True to Kim Jong Il's  wishes, girls in the capital city of Pyongyang and discharged soldiers from across the country voluntarily proceed to any work-sites, including villages on the northern highland,  remote coal and ore mines.  This indicates that the north is the only society pervaded with loyalty and filial piety on our planet, in which all servicemen and people breathe and behave  according to his intention and devote all their wisdom and energy to upholding his leadership.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   Such a reality in the north is the result of Kim Jong Il's  politics of loyalty and filial piety.   The 21st century will be a century of loyalty and filial piety in which  not only the Korean nation but mankind will follow the great Kim Jong Il.
